            <abstract>
                <p>Divinatory text predicting different events, mostly of unfortunate character, that will happen or not depending on the day of the 
                    week on which the feast day of St John the Baptist falls, similar to <ref type="work" corresp="LIT6702MashafaKobor"/>,
                    <ref type="work" corresp="LIT5048Hassabat#Kobor"/> (in the form <foreign xml:lang="gez">መጽሐፈ፡ ኮቦር፡</foreign>, and texts in 
                    <ref type="mss" corresp="CamOr1883">CUL Or. 1883, f. 37v</ref> (cf. <bibl><ptr target="bm:Ullendorff1961Catalogue"/>
                    <citedRange unit="item">LVIII</citedRange><citedRange unit="page">58-59</citedRange></bibl>),
                    Éthiopien 590 (Griaule 282) = Strelcyn 590, f. 34v (cf. <bibl><ptr target="bm:Strelcyn1954Griaule"/>
                    <citedRange unit="item">590,2</citedRange><citedRange unit="page">174-175</citedRange></bibl>, indicated as "Asāba
                    kobar, en amarique") as well as
                    Wellcome XVII, from f. 62r to 62v  (cf. <bibl><ptr target="bm:Strelcyn1972Wellcome"/>
                    <citedRange unit="item">XVII, 35</citedRange><citedRange unit="page">39-42</citedRange></bibl>).</p>
